While the dialogue was a bit unpolished, which I am sure will develop at you write more, this was thematically evocative enough that I don't especially care or mind.

I do agree with NatVoltaic's point about the Ezriel character feeling like they got the short end of the development stick.

Both of those criticisms aside, this is a thorough exploration of the theme in a way that naturally brought out emotion through character interaction rather than blunt force shock. The body horror was good early although some of the  was a bit repetitive in a couple of points.

That's a +1 from me.







